## Change 2: `replay_margins.m`

Signature: `replay_margins(json_path, run_dir, out_dir)` — bash writes a JSON sidecar so we can use built-in `jsondecode`.

Main flow:

```matlab
function replay_margins(json_path, run_dir, out_dir)
here = fileparts(mfilename('fullpath'));
addpath(here);  addpath(fullfile(here,'utils'));
set(0,'DefaultFigureVisible','off');

spec   = jsondecode(fileread(json_path));        % .axes .loops .mc.* .fw.*
S      = load(fullfile(run_dir, 'plants.mat'));
plants = S.plants;
fmin   = plants.cfg.fmin_Hz;
fmax   = plants.cfg.fmax_Hz;

axes_filter  = pick(spec, 'axes',  {'roll','pitch','yaw'});
loops_filter = pick(spec, 'loops', {'rate','attitude'});

rows = {};
for mode = {'mc','fw'}
    m = mode{1};
    if ~isfield(plants, m) || ~isfield(spec, m); continue; end
    fig_dir = fullfile(out_dir, 'figures', m);
    if ~isfolder(fig_dir); mkdir(fig_dir); end

    for ax = axes_filter
        a = ax{1};
        if ~isfield(plants.(m), a) || ~isfield(spec.(m), a); continue; end
        pr = plants.(m).(a).rate;
        gains = spec.(m).(a);
        [C_rate, C_att] = build_C_from_gains(m, gains);

        if any(strcmp(loops_filter,'rate')) && pr.ok && ~isempty(C_rate)
            L = analyze_loop(pr.tf_pade, C_rate, fmin, fmax);
            replay_plot(L, fig_dir, m, a, 'rate');
            rows{end+1} = row(m, a, 'rate', L);
        end
        if any(strcmp(loops_filter,'attitude')) && pr.ok && ~isempty(C_rate) && ~isempty(C_att)
            T_rate  = feedback(series(C_rate, pr.tf_pade), 1);
            G_outer = T_rate * tf(1, [1 0]);
            L = analyze_loop(G_outer, C_att, fmin, fmax);
            replay_plot(L, fig_dir, m, a, 'attitude');
            rows{end+1} = row(m, a, 'attitude', L);
        end
    end
end
write_replay_margins(fullfile(out_dir,'margins.txt'), rows, run_dir, spec);
end
```

Helpers (same file, kept short):

- **`build_C_from_gains(mode, g)`** — re-implements the 8-line formulas from `build_controller_tf.m` lines 31-40 (mc) and 71-80 (fw):
  - mc: `C_rate = K*(Kp + Ki/s + Kd*s/(tau_d*s+1))`, `C_att = tf(Kp_att, 1)`
  - fw: `C_rate = Kp + Ki/s + Kd*s/(tau_d*s+1)`, `C_att = tf(Kp_att, 1)`
  - `tau_d = 1/(2*pi*dterm_cutoff_Hz)`
  - Source-of-truth comment points back to `build_controller_tf.m`.
- **`replay_plot(L, fig_dir, mode, axis, loop)`** — emits 3 figures (bode of L from `L.L_response`/`L.w_grid`, `nichols(L.L); ngrid`, `step(L.T, t_end)`) saved as `{mode}_{axis}_{loop}_{bode,nichols,step}.png` + `.fig`. Style mirrors `make_plots.m` (`new_fig`/`save_fig` patterns duplicated locally — small enough not to refactor).
- **`write_replay_margins(path, rows, run_dir, spec)`** — writes header (run_dir, timestamp, fmin/fmax, axes/loops filter) then three columns: `Mode Axis Loop  GM_dB  PM_deg  VM`. Echoes the gains used per (mode, axis).
- **`pick(s, key, default)`** — `jsondecode` returns char arrays sometimes wrapped in cells; normalize to cellstr. Returns `default` if the field is absent.

**Why duplicate controller formula instead of calling `build_controller_tf.m` with a synthesized `containers.Map`?** `build_controller_tf` reads PX4 names (`MC_ROLLRATE_K` etc.) and warns on every missing param. Mapping YAML→PX4 names is fragile and noisy. The formula is 8 lines and stable — a one-line comment in `build_C_from_gains` pointing back to `build_controller_tf.m` keeps the source-of-truth clear.

