```yaml
# Path to the run_sysid output directory that contains plants.mat
run_dir: /home/choudhury/tools/dev/sysID_matlab/output/log_4_2026-5-13-15-46-26_20260514_170504

# Optional filters. Default: all axes, both loops.
axes:  [roll, pitch, yaw]
loops: [rate, attitude]

# MC gains: K is the outer scaling (see MC_*RATE_K in PX4); Kp_att maps MC_*_P.
mc:
  roll:  {K: 1.0, Kp: 1.0, Ki: 0.2, Kd: 0.00163, Kp_att: 1.2, dterm_cutoff_Hz: 30}
  pitch: {K: 1.0, Kp: 0.8, Ki: 0.6, Kd: 0.0,     Kp_att: 4.8, dterm_cutoff_Hz: 30}
  yaw:   {K: 0.4, Kp: 1.9, Ki: 0.5, Kd: 0.005,   Kp_att: 0.6, dterm_cutoff_Hz: 30}

# FW gains: no K (rate loop is Kp+Ki/s+Kd*s); Kp_att = 1/FW_*_TC if you use TC.
fw:
  roll:  {Kp: 0.08, Ki: 0.10, Kd: 0.0, Kp_att: 2.0, dterm_cutoff_Hz: 30}
  pitch: {Kp: 0.08, Ki: 0.10, Kd: 0.0, Kp_att: 2.0, dterm_cutoff_Hz: 30}
  yaw:   {Kp: 0.05, Ki: 0.10, Kd: 0.0, Kp_att: 1.0, dterm_cutoff_Hz: 30}
```

To analyze just one channel: set `axes: [roll]` and `loops: [rate]`.

